{
  "stem": "9730.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He knew exactly where and when a certain express train would stop at a certain station.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- and that-- that all helped him a great deal later in his profession.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was Max.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My-- did you want me to talk about my sister?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My sister's name was Irmgard.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We-- for short, we called her Gertie.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she decided to go into nursing, and also left home-- oh, I forget now when, but I would think in-- in the early '30s. '34, possibly-- '33, '34-- and went to Stuttgart for nurse's training.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And because she could gradually see-- well, we all became aware that this was the handwriting on the wall, there was no future, especially for young persons, Jews, in Germany.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We all sort of mentally and actually prepared ourselves for emigration.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never-- they were not alive.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My-- my mother was actually an orphan.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And and my father's parents-- well, my grandfather died 18 years before I was born.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my grandmother died at-- at the end of World War I, in 1918.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When she knew that all her sons were coming home, she made a statement, well, now I can die, knowing that they are all safe.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- and a few weeks later, and before any of them came home, she went down to the basement-- we had a basement, of course, a cellar-- and took a misstep and fell down the stairs and died, so she never got to see her sons.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But she knew that they were safe.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I-- [SIGHS] I was inclined to be playful.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I liked books a great deal.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I liked the theater and music.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I-- I was kind of carefree.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
